DataElement.preferredName: Animal Biological Entity Organism Strain ISO21090.ST.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A group of presumed common ancestry with clear-cut physiological but usually not morphological distinctions. EXAMPLE(S): The specific genotypic or phenotypic variant of an animal. Minnesota5 (swine strain), DXL (poultry strain), RB51 (vaccine strain of brucella abortus)
